TO COMPILE & EXECUTE:

1. CD into the root directory of our project(cs4500_a8/) that holds 
   this application's executable file(dan).

2. Execute one of the following commands:

    $ ./dan -f <path> -f <path>
    $ ./dan -f <path> -d <path>
    $ ./dan -d <path> -f <path>
    $ ./dan -d <path> -d <path>
    
    <path> is a linux path name for a file or directory within the CCIS 
    shared network.

    If "-f" precedes a <path>, then the <path> must be a resource file 
    that is in WAVE, MP3 or OGG format. 

    If "-d" precedes a <path>, then the <path> must be a directory path 
    which leads to a base resource file that is in WAVE, MP3 or OGG format.

3. In case of permissions issues, run the following command and return 
   step 2:

    $ chmod a+x dan 

------------------------------------------------------------------------
SOFTWARE AND MODULES USED:

All modules used were preinstalled on the CCIS Linux machines.
